b'Brian Flood'
b'Biography'
b'\nBrian Flood, News Bureau associate director, covers the College of Urban Planning and Public Affairs, and the humanities and social sciences in the College of Liberal Arts and Sciences.\nBrian Flood covers the College of Urban Planning and Public Affairs, and the humanities and social science departments in the College of Liberal Arts and Sciences.\nPrior to joining the UIC News Bureau staff in June 2004, he was director of public affairs at the School of the Art Institute of Chicago. Flood has also served clients in education and the arts as an account executive for a Chicago-based public relations firm.\nHe has a bachelor\xe2\x80\x99s degree in communication from DePaul University.\n '
b''
b'Brian Flood, News Bureau associate director, covers the College of Urban Planning and Public Affairs, and the humanities and social sciences in the College of Liberal Arts and Sciences.'
b'Brian Flood covers the College of Urban Planning and Public Affairs, and the humanities and social science departments in the College of Liberal Arts and Sciences.'
b'Prior to joining the UIC News Bureau staff in June 2004, he was director of public affairs at the School of the Art Institute of Chicago. Flood has also served clients in education and the arts as an account executive for a Chicago-based public relations firm.'
b'He has a bachelor\xe2\x80\x99s degree in communication from DePaul University.'
